                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "2. If question prefix is added and user deletes part of the QUESTION text e.g. \"QUE\". Should program take care of deleting the rest of the remaining text?", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "What ever the solution will be, the best way IMHO is to EXPLAIN to users what will be happening when check-box is checked.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I suggest to do something like: when user points mouse over \"check-box\" and waits for two seconds, there is some text displayed to explain what will happen, something like: \"Selecting Question check-box will add QUESTION prefix to the message.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Prefix means that you would like to have an answer from lecturer instead of other users participating in session debate.\"", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "P.S.", 
