        {
            "date": "2011-08-07 22:53:29", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Re: [Bug 793029] Re: Use check-box instead of Question button\nI think grofaty is correct that the text is too light when the\ncheckmark is not clicked and may confuse the user into thinking that\nthe checkbox is disabled, so reverted the status of this bug report.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "jsjgruber", 
            "email": "jsjgruber"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2011-08-08 06:05:14", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Re: Use check-box instead of Question button", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I can't see any benefit of adding bold/grayed out effect to checkbox.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "This effect is non-standard and not expected by end-user and also does not add any additional info to user, but in the other hand can add confusion of 'grayed out' effect.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I suggest to remove bold/grayed out effect and just use default check-boxes.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
